text: Henrytown is an unincorporated community in Fillmore County, in the U.S. state of Minnesota. ==History== Henrytown was platted in 1854. The community was named for Henry Onstine, an early settler. The Henrytown post office closed in 1902. https://www.findagrave.com/cgi-bin/fg.cgi?page=gr&GRid;=40281792 ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Fillmore County, Minnesota Category:Unincorporated communities in Minnesota
